The average rate of change of \(f\) on \([1,b]\) is
\[
\frac{f(b)-f(1)}{b-1}
=\frac{\bigl(4b^2-7\bigr)-\bigl(4\cdot1^2-7\bigr)}{b-1}
=\frac{4b^2-7-(-3)}{b-1}
=\frac{4b^2-4}{b-1}
=4\,\frac{b^2-1}{b-1}
=4(b+1),
\]
for \(b\neq1\).

The average rate of change of \(f\) on \([x,\,x+h]\) is

\[
\frac{f(x+h)-f(x)}{(x+h)-x}
=\frac{2(x+h)^2+1-\,\bigl(2x^2+1\bigr)}{h}
=\frac{2(x^2+2xh+h^2)-2x^2}{h}
=\frac{4xh+2h^2}{h}
=4x+2h.
\]

The average rate of change of 
 a(t)=1/(t+4) 
on [9, 9+h] is

\[
\frac{a(9+h)-a(9)}{(9+h)-9}
=\frac{\frac1{13+h}-\frac1{13}}{h}
=\frac{\frac{13-(13+h)}{13(13+h)}}{h}
=\frac{-h}{13(13+h)\,h}
=-\frac1{13(13+h)}.
\] 

So 

 Average rate of change = –1/[13(13+h)], 

valid for h≠0 (and so that 13+h≠0).

The average rate of change of \(j(x)=3x^3\) on \([1,1+h]\) is

\[
\frac{j(1+h)-j(1)}{(1+h)-1}
=\frac{3(1+h)^3-3\cdot1^3}{h}
=\frac{3\bigl((1+h)^3-1\bigr)}{h}
=\frac{3\bigl(1+3h+3h^2+h^3-1\bigr)}{h}
=\frac{3(3h+3h^2+h^3)}{h}
=9+9h+3h^2.
\]

The average rate of change of \(h\) on \([-2,4]\) is

\[
\frac{h(4)-h(-2)}{4-(-2)}
=\frac{\bigl(5-2\cdot4^2\bigr)-\bigl(5-2\cdot(-2)^2\bigr)}{6}
=\frac{(-27)-(-3)}{6}
=\frac{-24}{6}
=-4.
\]

The average rate of change of \(g\) over \([-3,3]\) is

\[
\frac{g(3)-g(-3)}{3-(-3)}
=\frac{\bigl(3\cdot3^3-1\bigr)-\bigl(3\cdot(-3)^3-1\bigr)}{6}
=\frac{80-(-82)}{6}
=\frac{162}{6}
=27.
\]

The average rate of change of \(f(x)=1/x\) over \([2,b]\) is

\[
\frac{f(b)-f(2)}{b-2}
=\frac{\tfrac1b-\tfrac12}{\,b-2\,}
=\frac{\tfrac{2-b}{2b}}{b-2}
=\frac{-(b-2)}{2b(b-2)}
=-\frac1{2b}.
\]

We set this equal to \(-\tfrac1{10}\):

\[
-\frac1{2b}=-\frac1{10}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
\frac1{2b}=\frac1{10}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
2b=10
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
b=5.
\]
